                  <lb n="3"/><persName><name key="Primitivus" type="cognomen"><choice><reg>Primitivo</reg><orig>Primitibo</orig></choice></name></persName> bene merenti <add place="right">qui <expan><abbr>f</abbr><ex cert="low">uit</ex><note>QUI F ANO, possible abbreviation for qui fuit annorum, as attested in two similar inscriptions discovered near Rome.  See <bibl><ptr type="rest-of-bibl" target="#CIL_VI"/>CIL <biblScope type="item">14417</biblScope></bibl> and <bibl><ptr type="rest-of-bibl" target="#ICUR"/> ICUR <biblScope type="item">ns 1.3455</biblScope></bibl>.</note></expan> <expan><abbr>an</abbr><ex cert="low">n</ex><abbr>o</abbr><ex cert="low">rum</ex></expan></add>
                  <lb n="4"/><add place="left"><num value="40">XL</num></add> <choice><reg>cum</reg><orig>qum</orig></choice>quo vixit annis <num value="12">XII</num> <expan><abbr>me</abbr><ex>n</ex><abbr>s</abbr><ex>ibus</ex></expan>
                  <lb n="5"/><num value="8">VIII</num>diebus <num value="7">VII</num> et discentes
                  <lb n="6"/>fecerunt <persName><name type="cognomen" key="Felix">Felix</name></persName> et <persName><name type="cognomen" key="Maximinus">Maximi
                  <lb n="7" break="no"/>nus</name></persName> magistro bene merenti.</ab>
         </div>
         </div>
         <div type="translation" xml:lang="en">
            <p>To the Shades of the Dead. Faustina made (this) for her most dear and well-deserving husband Primitivus, who was forty years old, with whom she lived twelve years, eight months, seven days; and also Felix and Maximinus, students, made (this) for their well-deserving teacher.</p>
            </div>
